    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="num">13.1M</div>
      <div class="lbl">tokens used</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="num">~63%</div>
      <div class="lbl">non-task work</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="section-label">The loop</p>
  <div class="loop-section">
    <p class="loop-intro">
      The pattern in this session was rarely prompt → answer → done. It was usually some version of this:
    </p>
    <div class="loop-row">
      <div class="loop-box">intent</div>
      <div class="loop-arrow">→</div>
      <div class="loop-box">inspect</div>
      <div class="loop-arrow">→</div>
      <div class="loop-box">adjust</div>
      <div class="loop-arrow">→</div>
      <div class="loop-box">retry</div>
      <div class="loop-arrow">→</div>
      <div class="loop-box loop-box-accent">loop</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="section-label">How the work actually broke down</p>
  <div class="chart-section">
    <div class="legend">
      <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-dot" style="background:#2563eb"></span>Task</span>
      <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-dot" style="background:#7c3aed"></span>Correction</span>
      <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-dot" style="background:#dc2626"></span>Clarification</span>
      <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-dot" style="background:#16a34a"></span>Confirmation</span>
      <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-dot" style="background:#d97706"></span>Iteration</span>
    </div>
    <div class="bars">
      <div class="bar-row">
        <div class="bar-label">Task</div>
        <div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" style="background:#2563eb; width:37%">37%</div></div>
        <div class="bar-count">158 msgs</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bar-row">
        <div class="bar-label">Correction</div>
        <div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" style="background:#7c3aed; width:23%">23%</div></div>
        <div class="bar-count">98 msgs</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bar-row">
        <div class="bar-label">Iteration</div>
        <div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" style="background:#d97706; width:17%">17%</div></div>
        <div class="bar-count">74 msgs</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bar-row">
        <div class="bar-label">Clarification</div>
        <div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" style="background:#dc2626; width:12%">12%</div></div>
        <div class="bar-count">52 msgs</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bar-row">
        <div class="bar-label">Confirmation</div>
        <div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" style="background:#16a34a; width:10%">10%</div></div>
        <div class="bar-count">44 msgs</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="section-label">Browse moments from the session</p>
  <div class="explorer">
    <div class="explorer-header">
      <span class="explorer-header-title">Session messages</span>
      <span class="explorer-header-hint">click any row to see why it matters</span>
    </div>
    <div class="filter-row">
      <button class="filter-btn active" onclick="filterMsgs('all', this)">All</button>
      <button class="filter-btn task" onclick="filterMsgs('task', this)">Task</button>
      <button class="filter-btn clarify" onclick="filterMsgs('clarify', this)">Clarification</button>
      <button class="filter-btn iterate" onclick="filterMsgs('iterate', this)">Iteration</button>
      <button class="filter-btn confirm" onclick="filterMsgs('confirm', this)">Confirmation</button>
      <button class="filter-btn correction" onclick="filterMsgs('correction', this)">Correction</button>
    </div>
    <div class="msg-list" id="msgList"></div>
    <div class="detail-panel" id="detailPanel">
      <div class="detail-label">Why this message matters</div>
      <div class="detail-text" id="detailText"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="insight">
    <strong>The pattern:</strong> None of this was failure. The model completed the work. The friction lived in the gap between assumption and reality — filenames, directory structure, visual intent, and changing state. Tapes made that gap visible.
  </div>

  <script>
    const messages = [
      {
        role: 'user', type: 'clarify', time: 'Mar 18',
        text: 'do you have a teleport command that pulls conversations from project conversations?',
        detail: 'This is discovery overhead. Before any real task work could happen, the session had to establish what Claude Code could and could not access.'
      },
      {
        role: 'assistant', type: 'correction', time: 'Mar 18',
        text: 'I can\'t directly access Claude.ai Projects — there\'s no integration between Claude Code and Claude.ai\'s project/conversation history.',
        detail: 'This is a correction, but it is also structural alignment. The shared map of the environment had to be repaired before the work could move forward.'
      },
      {
        role: 'user', type: 'task', time: 'Mar 18',
        text: 'I have a claude project with a blog post I want put into this repo. There are necessary diagrams. I want to hand the work of uploading and adding off to you.',
        detail: 'This is the actual task request. It arrives only after the session spends time establishing what the model can actually see and do.'
      },
      {
        role: 'user', type: 'correction', time: 'Mar 18',
        text: 'they\'re svgs. You can find them in documents/ai blogpost',
        detail: 'A small correction, but an important one. The model had created placeholder PNG assumptions. Reality turned out to be SVGs. That mismatch required another pass.'
      },
      {
        role: 'assistant', type: 'correction', time: 'Mar 18',
        text: 'Two filenames don\'t match what\'s in the post: ai-llms-model.svg (not ai-llms-models.svg) and context_window.svg (not context-window.svg).',
        detail: 'This is state alignment in plain view. The task itself was simple. The extra work came from reconciling what the model assumed against what actually existed on disk.'
      },
      {
        role: 'user', type: 'confirm', time: 'Mar 18',
        text: 'does the 2026 folder exist? I don\'t see it',
        detail: 'This adds no new task progress. It is confirmation work: checking whether a previous change actually exists in the world the user can see.'
      },
      {
        role: 'user', type: 'task', time: 'Mar 20',
        text: 'create a new PR that updates the docs to replace ./tapes.db with ./tapes.sqlite throughout the docs.',
        detail: 'This is a low-alignment task. It is precise, constrained, and technical. In this session, work like this generally moved faster than visual or ambiguous tasks.'
      },
      {
        role: 'user', type: 'iterate', time: 'Mar 27',
        text: 'Keep the current design. Add 6–10 total CSS-only twinkles across the component. Make them sparse, elegant, warm-gold/ivory, and subtle. No glitter, no icons, no busy animation, no JS changes.',
        detail: 'This is iteration layered with accumulated context. The growing constraint list suggests earlier passes taught the user what had to be ruled out explicitly.'
      },
      {
        role: 'assistant', type: 'correction', time: 'Mar 27',
        text: 'The sparkles are blurry glowing halos (8–20px blur), not sharp 1–2px dots — mine are invisible at that size. The active element has a dramatic ambient glow extending well beyond its border.',
        detail: 'This is semantic alignment. The word “sparkles” was not precise enough by itself. The session had to work toward a shared visual meaning.'
      },
      {
        role: 'user', type: 'iterate', time: 'Mar 27',
        text: 'it doesn\'t look like the image I gave you. Are you able to see the image?',
        detail: 'This is what iteration looks like when shared reality is still unstable. Before design can improve, both sides have to confirm they are even working from the same reference.'
      },
      {
        role: 'user', type: 'iterate', time: 'Mar 27',
        text: 'maybe the issue is the color palette. It looks dirty, not magical. the sparkles should be bright, like a star or a light bulb.',
        detail: 'This is exactly the kind of work that gets hidden inside “prompting.” It is not just asking for output. It is translating vague visual feeling into something actionable.'
      },
      {
        role: 'assistant', type: 'correction', time: 'Mar 27',
        text: 'The issue is clear — the palette is all muted amber-brown. Stars and light bulbs have a near-white/bright-yellow core. I need to shift sparkle colors toward bright white-yellow with high opacity.',
        detail: 'This is a successful semantic correction. The technical fix is easy once the meaning is shared. The hard part was getting there.'
      }
    ];

    let currentFilter = 'all';
    let selectedIdx = null;

    function filterMsgs(type, btn) {
      currentFilter = type;
      document.querySelectorAll('.filter-btn').forEach(b => b.classList.remove('active'));
      btn.classList.add('active');
      selectedIdx = null;
      document.getElementById('detailPanel').classList.remove('visible');
      renderList();
    }

    function selectMsg(idx) {
      selectedIdx = idx;
      const m = messages[idx];
      document.getElementById('detailText').textContent = m.detail;
      document.getElementById('detailPanel').classList.add('visible');
      renderList();
    }

    function renderList() {
      const list = document.getElementById('msgList');
      const filtered = messages
        .map((m, i) => ({ ...m, origIdx: i }))
        .filter(m => currentFilter === 'all' || m.type === currentFilter);

      if (!filtered.length) {
        list.innerHTML = '<div style="padding:20px 16px; font-size:13px; color:#aaa;">No messages in this category.</div>';
        return;
      }

      list.innerHTML = filtered.map(m => `
        <div class="msg-row${selectedIdx === m.origIdx ? ' selected' : ''}" onclick="selectMsg(${m.origIdx})">
          <span class="badge badge-${m.role}">${m.role}</span>
          <span class="badge badge-${m.type}">${m.type}</span>
          <span class="msg-text">${m.text}</span>
          <span class="msg-time">${m.time}</span>
        </div>
      `).join('');
    }

    renderList();
  </script>
</div>
